Package: gtkspell
Version: 2.0.4
Revision: 1
Description: Snow for your x11 desktop and windows
DescDetail: <<
GtkSpell provides MSWord/MacOSX-style highlighting of misspelled words
in a GtkTextView widget. Right-clicking a misspelled word pops up a
menu of suggested replacements.

GtkSpell also provides a library, allowing use in other Gtk project.
<<
DescPort: <<
Gtkspell can use aspell, or ispell if aspell isn't found.  Fink's
aspell does not include any language, so if we want aspell we must
depend on "one of" the language packages as well as aspell
itself. Fink does not provide a mechanism for boolean grouping, (we
cannot say "Depends: (aspell, aspell-en) | ispell") so we'll just
require (the more advanced) aspell/etc.
<<
